ace="Courier New, Courier, mono"><strong>Download           information on all the geocaches nearby zipcode 27513 that I have not           completed, and output it in EasyGPS format</strong></font></p>        <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">And it will write out a .loc           file to be used with <a href="http://www.easygps.com/">EasyGPS</a>,           with all your nearby waypoints with intelligently named waypoints, so           that you can transfer them straight to your GPS unit. You can also generate           more complex queries such as:</font></p>        <p><font color="#777777" face="Courier New, Courier, mono"><strong>Download           all of the geocaches in North Carolina, that have a difficulty higher           than 3, contain travel bugs, match the keywords of river, stream, ocean,           or lake, and output it into a basic HTML format so I can browse it on           my phone. </strong></font></p>        <p><font color="#000000" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">GeoToad is           currently limited to a command-line client, which operates in Windows,           Mac OS X, Linux, and other UNIX flavors. We're working on a web client           that can be used from cellphones, and are looking for volunteers to           write graphical front-ends.</font></p>        <p><font color="#3C471E" size="5"><strong>GeoToad News:</strong></font></p>        <p><strong><font color="#638C05" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">First           Public Release - 2.3.0</font><font color="#0E0E9E" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><br>          <font color="#979797" size="2">Thomas</font> </font></strong><font color="#0E0E9E" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><font size="2">-           <font color="#000000">26apr2003 11:09</font></font></font></p>        <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Our first public release           of GeoToad is finally out the door. A couple of important changes have           been made recently:</font></p>      </div>      <ul>        <li>           <div align="left"><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Drastically             better documentation. (still not good enough)</font></div>        </li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Updated the list of formats           we support through gpsbabel (not all tested)</font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">We now will lookup the country/state           codes for you. </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">We now export to a file           named geotoad_output.(format extension) instead of stdout if you give           it no arguments.</font></li>      </ul>      <div align="left">        <p>Please submit any bug reports, confusion, or suggestions to <a href="mailto:geotoad%2Bweb@toadstool.sh">geotoad+web@toadstool.sh</a></p>        <p><strong><font color="#638C05" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">New           Web Site!</font><font color="#0E0E9E" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><br>          <font color="#979797" size="2">Thomas</font> </font></strong><font color="#0E0E9E" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><font size="2">-           <font color="#000000">26apr2003 09:42</font></font></font></p>        <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">We've now actually got a           website up, Huzzah! Yes, it's a pretty lame little site, I'm not feeling           overly creative at the moment. Maybe someone with more inspiration and           time can step up to bat and make a better site design. I feel kind of           bad having this site done with normal HTML markup, rather than some           nice CSS magic. I just have been working on the code too much :)</font></p>        <p>&nbsp;</p>        <p>&nbsp;</p>        <p>&nbsp;</p>      </div></td>    <td> <div align="left"></div>      </td>  </tr></table></body></html>